{"questionId":"27809","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>DeVaughn throws a javelin in a school track and field competition.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/cdd45b709d6f7d19966199a7c8a9633d21aa0806.png\"></p>\n<p>The height, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>, of the front tip of the javelin above the ground, in metres, is modelled by the&nbsp;following quadratic function,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the time in seconds after the javelin is thrown.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the height of the front tip of the javelin at the time it is thrown.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mtext>m</mtext></mfenced></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27809","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the height of the front tip of the javelin at the time it is thrown.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Intersection of lines, equations of perpendicular bisectors","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}